dspace-cli.title: JRuby cannot be used to run DSpace CLI tasks on the DataSpace QA environment

comments.body:
In order to gain admin. privileges, I needed to create a separate, dedicated admin. account using the Java command-line interface (please see `create-administrator` on https://wiki.lyrasis.org/display/DSDOC5x/Command+Line+Operations). I have granted `jrg5` and `kmcelwee` administrative privileges with this using JRuby:

```
irb(main):003:0> DSpace.login('dspace-admin2@princeton.edu')
=> nil
irb(main):004:0> person = DEPerson.find('jrg5@princeton.edu')
=> #<Java::OrgDspaceEperson::EPerson:0x70e00c84>
irb(main):005:0> person.getNetid
=> nil
irb(main):006:0> person.setNetid('jrg5')
=> nil
irb(main):007:0> person.update
=> nil
irb(main):008:0> DSpace.commit
=> nil
irb(main):009:0> person = DEPerson.find('kmcelwee@princeton.edu')
=> #<Java::OrgDspaceEperson::EPerson:0x156a147a>
irb(main):010:0> person.getNetid
=> "kmcelwee"
irb(main):011:0> java_import org.dspace.eperson.Group
=> [Java::OrgDspaceEperson::Group]
irb(main):012:0> admins = Java::OrgDspaceEperson::Group.find(DSpace.context, 1)
=> #<Java::OrgDspaceEperson::Group:0x27225261>
irb(main):013:0> admins.addMember(person)
=> nil
irb(main):014:0> admins.isMember(person)
=> true
irb(main):015:0> admins.update
=> nil
irb(main):016:0> DSpace.commit
=> nil
irb(main):017:0>
```

One should now able able to authenticate over the CAS and access the user dashboard:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/84833933-5290d980-affe-11ea-84b0-4024be87c774.png)

comments.body: **Source decision:**  Institution [Princeton University Library], identifier [bibid / component id]. @hackmastera will concentrate the two into one.  Discussed options with both Jennifer Baxmeyer and @escowles .

Question from @hackmastera confirm / deny whether we want language, coverage, subject:
(Note that in figgy coverage tends to mean geographic, but here it’s a date range):

- language: yes.  comply with requested ISO 639-2b standard 

- coverage: no. we provide the date(s) as part of mandatory fields, which should be sufficient.

- subject: it would be nice?But... Question: we pull subjects from the MARC records, but it does not look like we pull them for FA materials into figgy. If we provide subjects, does this mean we would have to provide them for FA content too? it looks like it works differently there.
@kelea99 I don't think we'd have to provide subjects for the FA content. The field appears fully optional.
